The mother of an unruly teen who was shipped to Siberia in 2011 has refused to bring the desperate 17-year-old back to America, claiming she didn't live up to her end of the bargain.

Natalie Roberts, 36, sent her daughter, Sofia Petrova, from Chantilly, Virginia, to live with her biological father in the frigid city of Novosibirsk after she failed at school, ran away from home and stole $1,000. But two-and-a-half years later, the stern mother insists the teen still hasn't learned her lesson, even though she claims her dad abused her.

'She had to meet two conditions to come back; finish school and show she's changed,' Roberts told People Magazine. 'She didn't.'

