Her
 appeals to the US embassy and Vladimir Putin's ombudsman for children, 
Pavel Astakhov, have all met with no response, she said. 

In October, she was tracked down by The Siberian Times to a Novosibirsk hostel where she lives and works a 60 hour week, including nights, to earn her keep and pay for her studies.

Now
 17, she penned a heartfelt letter to her mother in her latest desperate
 bid to be allowed back from Siberia where she says she has few friends 
and feels an outsider.

